| free_label_3 = | free_data_3 = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | embedded = }} The '''Yucatán Platform''' or '''Yucatán Shelf''' is a [[geologic province|geologic]] or [[Physiographic province|physiographic]] province, and a [[Platform (geology)|continental]] and [[carbonate platform]], in the [[Maya Block]] of the southernmost portion of the [[North American Plate]]. It comprises the [[Yucatán Peninsula]] and its [[continental shelf]], located between the [[Gulf of Mexico]] and the [[Caribbean Sea]].{{notetag|The terms ''Yucatán Platform'' and ''Yucatán Shelf'' are sometimes used as a synonyms for the Yucatán Peninsula, i.e., the exposed portion of the Yucatán Platform (e.g., in {{harvnb|Nairn|Stehli|1975|pp=257–258}} and {{harvnb|Bundschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=77|loc=fig. 3.1}}). This article does not employ said usage.}}
== Extent == The Yucatán Platform is commonly defined as the [[platform (geology)|continental platform]] constituted by the [[Yucatán Peninsula]] and its continental shelf.{{sfn|Miranda-Madrigal|Chavez-Cabello|2020|pp=187-189}}{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|pp=43-44}} As such, the margins of the continental shelf, or, more particularly, their {{convert|650|ft|m}} isobaths or depth contours, are often taken as the platform's submarine limits.{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|pp=43-44}} Its subaerial limits (on the Yucatán Peninsula) are less precisely fixed.{{citation needed|date=June 2022}}
The [[US Geological Survey]] have demarcated the limits of the Yucatán Platform.{{sfn|French|Schenk|2004|loc=doc. map}}{{sfn|French|Schenk|2006|loc=doc. map}} Their [[British Geological Survey|British]], [[Geology and Petroleum Department (Belize)|Belizean]], and [[Mexican Geological Survey|Mexican]] counterparts have not defined an equivalent geologic, physiographic, or geomorphic province or region.{{citation needed|date=June 2022}}
== Geography == === Political === The exposed or peninsular portion of the Yucatán Platform encompasses four [[districts of Belize]] (i.e., Corozal, Orange Walk, Belize, and Cayo), one [[Departments of Guatemala|department of Guatemala]] (i.e., Peten), and four [[states of Mexico]] (i.e., Quintana Roo, Yucatán, Campeche, and Tabasco).{{sfn|French|Schenk|2006|loc=doc. map}}{{sfn|French|Schenk|2004|loc=doc. map}} Its submarine portion encompasses the continental shelf which abuts those of the aforementioned districts with a coast.{{sfn|French|Schenk|2006|loc=doc. map}}{{sfn|French|Schenk|2004|loc=doc. map}}
=== Basins === At least three sedimentary basins have been identified in the Yucatán Platform, namely, the Campeche, Yucatán, and Peten{{nbnd}}Corozal.{{sfn|Evenick|2021|p=6|loc=fig. 4}}
=== Faults === At least six fault systems or zones have been identified in the Yucatán Platform, namely, the Holbox, Hondo, Ticul, Ring of Cenotes, Chemax{{nbnd}}Catoche, and La Libertad, with the first four of these considered prominent.{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|pp=32, 76}}
== Geology == === Formation === The Gulf of Mexico formed during a 70{{nbnd}}90 million year rifting of [[Pangaea]], which began some 240 [[million years ago]], during the [[Middle Triassic]], and ended some 170{{nbnd}}150 million years ago, during the [[Middle Jurassic|Middle]] or [[Late Jurassic]].{{sfn|Davidson|Pindell|Hull|2020|pp=3, 6}}{{sfn|Miranda-Madrigal|Chavez-Cabello|2020|p=183}} The subaerially exposed (i.e., peninsular) portion of the platform is thought to have been fully submarine up to some 30{{nbnd}}10 million years ago.{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|p=43}}
=== Layers === ==== Basement ==== The platform's [[Basement (geology)|crystalline basement]] is composed mainly of [[Precambrian]] to [[Palaeozoic]] granodiorite rocks.{{sfn|Davidson|Pindell|Hull|2020|p=3}}{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|pp=43-45}} It starts at a depth of some {{convert|2.3|mi|km}} in the centre-point of the platform's exposed or peninsular portion, but steeps down towards the platform's eastern and northwestern extremes, starting at a depth of {{convert|3.4|-|3.7|mi|km}} in the latter point.{{sfn|Miranda-Madrigal|Chavez-Cabello|2020|p=189}}{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|p=43}}
==== Cover ==== The platform's sedimentary cover is composed mainly of carbonates and evaporites formed during or after the [[Early Cretaceous]].{{sfn|Miranda-Madrigal|Chavez-Cabello|2020|pp=187-189}} It forms one of the largest deposits of carbonate minerals on Earth, with a depth range of {{convert|2.3|-|3.7|mi|km}} .{{sfn|Monroy-Rios|2020|pp=26, 43}}
